args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject impact or consideration functions as a contextual factor that must be weighed within the given ethical dilemma or decision context.
args.justification: In both relations, the subject (improved efficiency, productivity) is described as a positive aspect that functions as a contextual factor within ethical dilemmas in AI development. A single predicate 'is_contextual_factor_in' captures this shared semantics more precisely than the raw 'is_aspect_of'.

Both relations connect societal/economic impacts (efficiency, productivity) to an ethical dilemma construct as contextual factors. This is a recurring pattern where features or impacts form part of the context to be weighed in an ethical dilemma, warranting a dedicated class 'ethical_dilemma_context_relation'.

The relations do not express causality or composition but rather that certain impacts are part of the contextual landscape of an ethical dilemma. This fits a broad group for contextual or situational linkage, here labeled 'CONTEXTUALITY'.
